cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a method to improve model capacity without increasing inference-time complexity, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method is based on data locality and domain-specific models, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The proposed method is evaluated on an object detection benchmark, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) for labeling and annotation.
